<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1383214" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Obase.jpg?resize=500%2C281&#038;ssl=1" alt="Edo State: Obaseki’s Chief of Staff resigns" width="500" height="281" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Obase.jpg?w=775&amp;ssl=1 775w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Obase.jpg?resize=300%2C168&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Obase.jpg?resize=768%2C431&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Obase.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Obase.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Obase.jpg?resize=200%2C112&amp;ssl=1 200w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Chief of Staff to Governor Godwin Obaseki of Edo State, Mr. Taiwo Akerele, has resigned. It was gathered that his resignation is connected with the lingering crisis between the Governor and the APC National Chairman, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole. In his resignation letter dated 25th April 2020, Akerele said; “My decision to exit the government is based on administrative and governance grounds. “I am solid with His excellency Mr. Godwin Obaseki in his quest to transform Edo state. His mission and vision resonate with mine. “This is all I have to say, I will like to be given the opportunity to go private as I part ways administratively with the government based on principles. “I thank his Excellency for the opportunity given to me to serve in this capacity and also thanks to His Royal Majesty, Oba of Benin, Oba Ewuare II for his immense leadership and support during the period I served in this capacity. May his reign be long and peaceful. Amen.” vanguard The Oba of Lagos, Oba Rilwan Akiolu, has called for a peaceful resolution of the political impasse in Edo State, noting that such was necessary for the development and advancement of the state. Oba Akiolu said this on Sunday when the Edo State Governor, Mr. Godwin Obaseki led members… January 19, 2020 In "News" The Edo State Deputy Governor, Rt. Hon. Comrade Philip Shaibu, has described Governor Godwin Obaseki as a man of destiny with the capacity to transform the fortunes of the state. July 2, 2019 In "News" The federal government has given out over four million naira as start-up seed fund to 17 young innovators under the Social Investment Programme at the South-South Innovation Hub in Benin City, the Edo State capital. October 6, 2018 In "Business"